@thenorthface has signed an eight-year partnership with U.S. Ski & Snowboard, becoming the organization’s Official Performance Apparel Partner through 2034. The brand will outfit athletes, coaches, and staff across all 11 disciplines with competition outerwear, training apparel, accessories, and luggage for World Cup events, World Championships, and the Olympic and Paralympic Winter Games leading up to 2030 and 2034.⁠
⁠
The kits will feature technologies including Futurelight, Cloud Down insulation, Futurefleece, DryVent, and Gore-Tex, developed alongside U.S. Ski & Snowboard athletes. A consumer collection inspired by the partnership is set to launch in Fall 2026.

@ford Super Duty pickup truck is to automobiles what @carhartt Active Jackets are to fashion: rugged, reliable blue-collar icons with a cult following willing to pay top dollar for rare vintage models. Now the two are officially becoming one. The 2027 Ford Super Duty Carhartt Package, created with Carhartt mainline, essentially turns Ford’s toughest truck into a wearable workwear statement on wheels. Carhartt’s influence shows up most in the interior, where abrasion-resistant “canvas inspired” upholstery and triple-stitched detailing bring the brand’s hardwearing DNA into the cabin, while dark anodized trim and industrial-style finishes toughen up the exterior.⁠
⁠
The truck also marks the start of a long-term partnership between the two Detroit-born labels, whose original workshops sat just a mile apart. Beyond co-branded vehicles, the collaboration includes support for skilled trades programs through Ford Auto Tech Scholars initiatives, alongside bespoke workwear and “Super Duty” merch. Right now, that merch is limited to tees and hats, but the prospect of official Ford x Carhartt mechanic overalls already feels inevitable.

@jamesonus and @kidsuper brought their “super smooth” world to Williamsburg with a launch party that blended Brooklyn creativity, community, and football culture into one energetic night. Following the collaboration’s debut at Paris Fashion Week, the event celebrated the collection through interactive moments including a mini soccer tournament, custom KidSuper merch, music, and plenty of Jameson flowing throughout the space.⁠
⁠
Rooted in KidSuper founder Colm Dillane’s colorful vision of Brooklyn, the collection mixes sporty jerseys, hoodies, and tracksuits with the playful, expressive spirit both brands share. The Jameson x KidSuper collection is available online starting May 8.

